    <h2>Answer</h2>
<p>
    If I utilize the term "all", I can delete "color 0.2s linear" on the following code: "transition: background .3s ease, color 0.2s linear; " <br>
    I will need to know the term when learning the transition. I know that ease starts at a slow speed, then becomes faster, and then ends at a slow speed. The liner keeps the same speed. Ease-in and ease-out are similar, but ease-in starts at a slow speed, and ease-in ends at a slow speed. The last item is the cubic-bezier, which specifies your transition appearance value.

